The man took her hand and led her out of the house of death.
Once they were back out in the forest, the man held up the whistle again.
"You have three more uses out of this whistle; use them wisely." He assured her, laying it in her palm again, "I won't be far."
As he walked away, he called over his shoulder, "By the way, be safer walking across the street!"
He left Little Red Riding Hood standing confused and scared, but safe.
